Title : Thelma Records
Text : '''Thelma Records''' was a record label in [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]] from 1962 until 1966. Recordings included [[Emanuel Laskey]], [[Eddie Hill (singer)|Eddie Hill]], [[Rose Batiste]], [[Richard Street & the Distants]], [[Alberta Adams]], [[The Fabulous Pips]] and [[Martha Star]].<ref>45 Discography for Thelma Records at [http://www.globaldogproductions.info/t/thelma.html Global Dog Productions], retrieved May 1, 2014</ref> The label was formed by Hazel Coleman, mother of [[Berry Gordy|Berry Gordy's]] first wife Thelma Coleman.<ref>See, for example, Ribowsky, Mark (2010) ''The Supremes: A Saga of Motown Dreams, Success, and Betrayal'', Da Capo Press, page 60 {{ISBN|9780306818738}} [https://books.google.com.au/books?id=f0fIGoFtdVIC&pg=PA60&lpg=PA60&dq=%22thelma+records%22&source=bl&ots=a8yzqqQUcC&sig=2aYHWqS8cA4_lbPptHBXJkpKuzo&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwihtYP--5zQAhUBzpQKHWhDCKUQ6AEIeDAW#v=onepage&q=%22thelma%20records%22&f=false (excerpted at Google Books)] and Interview with [[Don Davis (record producer)|Don Davis]] at [http://www.soulexpress.net/dondavis_interview.htm soulexpress.net], retrieved November 9, 2016</ref>

